# Heart Disease S6E2: Trinity Protocol v3.3.1 (UCI Integrated)

Successfully upgraded the pipeline to version **3.3.1**, incorporating the large UCI heart disease dataset as ground-truth training signal.

## 🚀 Key Improvements

- **UCI Data Integration**: Added 101 high-quality clinical samples from the UCI repository.
- **Categorical Mapping**: Implemented a robust translation layer to convert UCI clinical strings (e.g., "typical angina") into competition-standard numerical codes.
- **Pseudo-Labeling (V6)**: High-confidence test predictions (>0.95 or <0.05) are added back to the training set for a second training pass, improving model sensitivity.
- **Dual Ensemble**: CatBoost (2 seeds) + LightGBM (1 seed) with optimal alpha blending.

## 📊 Performance Insights

The dry-run on the expanded dataset (630,101 rows) confirmed stable training across both Phase 1 and Phase 2.

